Review: less often now, but once every year, once every two years, i have a dream where i'm hanging out with my brother. and invariably i spend it filling him in on all the pop culture developments since he died
got this year's Big December Cry. Feeling much better about that than I do about last year's winner: The Whale
could in fact have done with even more hanging out and less direct statement of thesis - usually successful with occasional stretches toward the sublime
can't say i particularly care for the man
aww man this is gonna go right over their heads isn't it
there's like 1.5 good musical theater songs and a heist what do you want from me
as with all sketch movies, there are highs and lows, but the laughs and humanity are so there throughout with a sweet mean-spiritedness that is perfectly attuned to how it is to be a person and stuff
Beautiful little shot of empathy straight to the dome
there are less technically competent musicals. there are probably not many worse screenplays to expose a child to
Hilarious, incredible technicolor production design, and maybe the most ethically correct movie of recent memory
